brucew@chattanooga.net (Bruce Wilkey) wrote:


>>I'm about to buy a P75/PCI system. They company offers 256K 2nd level 
>>cache or EDO RAM as configuration.
>>What should I take ?


>IF, repeat, IF their motherboard uses the Trident chipset, the use of EDO 
>Ram can provide an increase of thirty percent (30%) in performance.  
>Check out the article in PC Computing, August, 1995 page 44.  That would 
>far exceed the performance boost of a second level cache, I would 
>think...

Hardly...This is the "official" story on EDO, but the truth
is nowhere near "30%", at least not in any of the systems I've seen.
More like 3% in a system already equipped with an L2 cache.  
EDO/no cache is still slower than DRAM+L2 cache.  Don't confuse
EDRAM with EDO-RAM.
